    "summary": "This IDM specifies the information required to support the cost estimation of doors in building projects. It defines the exchange requirements for geometric properties, material and hardware specifications, quantities, and cost data associated with doors, enabling accurate budget preparation and procurement planning during the design and production stages of a project.",
    "revisionHistory": [
      {
        "date": "2026-05-22",
        "description": "Initial creation"
      }
    ],
    "changeLogs": [
      {
        "id": "log-1",
        "changeDateTime": "2026-05-22T00:00:00",
        "changeSummary": "Initial creation",
        "changedBy": "author-1",
        "changes": []
      }
    ],
    "contributors": [],
    "copyright": "Copyright 2026 Building Informatics Group (BIG), Yonsei University",
    "keywords": [],
    "relatedStandards": [],
    "externalReferences": [],
    "objectives": "The aim of this IDM is to define the minimum information that must be exchanged between design authoring tools (e.g., architectural BIM software) and cost estimation tools when performing door cost estimation. The scope covers all door types in building envelopes and interior partitions including hinged, sliding, folding, revolving, and automatic doors. It addresses supply costs, installation costs, and hardware costs. Sub-structure works such as structural openings, lintels, and door frames cast into walls are outside the scope.",
    "aimAndScope": "The aim of this IDM is to define the minimum information that must be exchanged between design authoring tools (e.g., architectural BIM software) and cost estimation tools when performing door cost estimation. The scope covers all door types in building envelopes and interior partitions including hinged, sliding, folding, revolving, and automatic doors. It addresses supply costs, installation costs, and hardware costs. Sub-structure works such as structural openings, lintels, and door frames cast into walls are outside the scope.",
    "benefits": "Enables automated extraction of door quantities and properties from BIM models, reducing manual take-off effort and improving cost estimation accuracy. Supports early cost feedback during the design phase and provides a structured basis for procurement planning, hardware scheduling, and tender documentation. Fire door and access-controlled door requirements can be systematically captured and priced.",
    "limitations": "This IDM does not cover automated door systems requiring specialist engineering design (e.g., revolving door drives, high-speed industrial doors). Costs for associated structural works, door frames cast into masonry or concrete, and ironmongery schedules beyond the hardware set classification are outside the scope. Regional price variations must be accounted for separately by the cost estimator.",
